  <brief_title>Study to Evaluate Frozen Versus Refrigerated MMRV (Combined Measles, Mumps, Rubella, and Varicella) Investigational Vaccine (V221-016)</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Comparison of the Safety, Tolerability, and Immunogenicity of a Refrigerator-Stable Measles, Mumps, Rubella, and Varicella Combination Vaccine V221 (Refrigerated) Versus V221 (Frozen) in Healthy Children</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Merck Sharp &amp; Dohme Corp.</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Merck Sharp &amp; Dohme Corp.</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to demonstrate that an investigational refrigerated vaccine with
      measles, mumps, rubella, and varicella is well tolerated and has similar immune response when
      compared to a frozen vaccine with measles, mumps, rubella, and varicella.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
